The Ipsos Pulse of the People survey carried out last November identified four items in particular that had become more unaffordable: saving for retirement paying for a home education and food.Less than a third of the 3 416 respondents said they looked to the future with hope. And 62% were critical of the government's management of the economy."It is clear that all South Africans regardless of income feel the pressure of rising prices " said Ipsos.